<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-186-052 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 542 222</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  April 1991 v16 n4 p259(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Low-cost 3-D animation materializes for PC users. (SoftwareReview) (Autodesk's 3D Studio; includes related article on thetesting of the software) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Loveria, Greg.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The $2,995 3D Studio from Autodesk (Sausalito, CA) is a completeprofessional three-dimensional modeling and animation softwarepackage useful for a wide range of design, animation andmultimedia applications.andP;  The software includes five integratedmodules: 2-D shaper, 3-D extruder, 3-D editor, materials editorand keyframer.andP;  Functions available in each of these modules arediscussed.andP;  Other examples of 3D Studio's numerous featuresinclude pull-down and side menus accessed by mouse or digitizertablet, import and export of DXF wire-frame models, tree-basedcommand structure, hierarchical animation capabilities and goodtutorial and 'massive' documentation.andP;  The minimum host systemrequired is an Intel 80386- or 80486-based IBM PC or compatiblewith a math coprocessor, 3Mbytes of random-access memory, 20Mbytesof free hard disk space, compatible 80386 BIOS and VGA display.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Autodesk Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    ACAD.andO;Product:   3D Studio (Multimedia software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationGraphics SoftwareAnimationThree-Dimensional Graphics.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Product review summary, minimum host system required and vendordata. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>